1
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:06,690
[Pretty Boy]

2
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:09,570
[Episode 14]

3
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:12,460
Being too smart makes you look less cute.

4
00:02:18,260 --> 00:02:19,310
I was wrong.

5
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,260
You have a special relationship with him, right?

6
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,470
I can't hide it from you.

7
00:02:33,770 --> 00:02:35,170
To be honest with you,

8
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:36,329
he is my father.

9
00:02:37,620 --> 00:02:39,210
From how intimate you were,

10
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,810
I already had a rough idea.

11
00:02:41,450 --> 00:02:44,079
I came here to save him.

12
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:45,900
Then your relationship with the son of the late Emperor...

13
00:02:47,810 --> 00:02:49,150
We're kind of...

14
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,380
Friends, I guess,

15
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:54,900
Close friends.

16
00:02:54,930 --> 00:02:57,320
And your father's organization...

17
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,630
I'm not a death warrior.

18
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:03,580
Normally, father and daughter won't both be death warriors.

19
00:03:04,220 --> 00:03:07,170
I'm the nominal person in charge of this operation.

20
00:03:07,330 --> 00:03:09,610
But, you know...

21
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:12,290
It's already not easy for you to come.

22
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,860
I guess you're kind of like a hostage prince.

23
00:03:16,570 --> 00:03:17,900
You feel that way too?

24
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:19,560
Your father is on such an important mission.

25
00:03:19,590 --> 00:03:21,920
How can the higher-ups rest assured without a hostage?

26
00:03:22,079 --> 00:03:24,050
It's an extra guarantee, I guess.

27
00:03:24,260 --> 00:03:26,360
I threatened them with my life this time,

28
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:27,470
or they wouldn't have let me come.

29
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:30,490
How did you learn about your father's arrest?

30
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,490
From my master.

31
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:34,570
I've been isolated in a place since I was little.

32
00:03:34,770 --> 00:03:36,600
Only my master taught me martial arts.

33
00:03:37,470 --> 00:03:40,329
He treats me like his own daughter.

34
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:41,810
What about your mother?

35
00:03:44,170 --> 00:03:44,940
I don't know.

36
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:46,920
My father said

37
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:49,990
my mother died due to obstructed labor when giving birth to me.

38
00:03:50,390 --> 00:03:51,310
If that's the case,

39
00:03:51,310 --> 00:03:53,630
you shouldn't know the son of the late Emperor.

40
00:03:53,650 --> 00:03:55,329
I've known him since childhood.

41
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,680
It's just he didn't know me.

42
00:04:00,060 --> 00:04:02,820
So, do you think the son of the late Emperor will show up?

43
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:06,500
I really don't know what he thinks.

44
00:04:06,930 --> 00:04:08,220
And I don't know

45
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,090
if this place of yours is a trap.

46
00:04:11,010 --> 00:04:12,600
We're showing our sincerity.

47
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:14,870
The Martial Arts World is changeable and treacherous.

48
00:04:15,650 --> 00:04:17,320
Who can believe what anyone says?

49
00:04:17,350 --> 00:04:19,570
I don't buy it, that you are showing sincerity.

50
00:04:19,810 --> 00:04:21,040
On the way here,

51
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:23,030
you've found out all about me.

52
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:27,990
Who said she wanted to make friends?

53
00:04:28,010 --> 00:04:30,130
No, I dare not.

54
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:52,290
That's right.

55
00:04:52,630 --> 00:04:54,140
Our nightwear

56
00:04:54,210 --> 00:04:55,790
was also made here.

57
00:05:11,070 --> 00:05:12,720
He seems afraid of you.

58
00:05:16,130 --> 00:05:17,450
I don't eat people,

59
00:05:17,470 --> 00:05:18,920
nor am I a robber.

60
00:05:19,110 --> 00:05:20,500
Why are you so afraid of me?

61
00:05:24,020 --> 00:05:24,820
Alright, alright.

62
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:25,840
Look at him.

63
00:05:25,910 --> 00:05:27,010
Don't scare him anymore.

64
00:05:27,470 --> 00:05:28,710
It's not easy for him either.

65
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:32,220
Tell us yourself,

66
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,670
did I scare you?

67
00:05:33,870 --> 00:05:36,560
When you argued with me over a few pennies last time,

68
00:05:36,620 --> 00:05:38,540
I ended up giving you more money, didn't I?

69
00:05:38,790 --> 00:05:39,940
Y-Yes.

70
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,690
You're very generous, Miss.

71
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,100
Young Master Wang, are you checking out new fabrics again?

72
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:56,450
You want to buy fabrics and make new clothes for me again?

73
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,050
The way you said it

74
00:05:59,210 --> 00:06:01,180
made it sound like I had an ulterior motive.

75
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:12,620
Let's go check out other stalls.

76
00:06:15,770 --> 00:06:16,670
I'm sorry.

77
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,390
Don't be so scared next time.

78
00:06:32,010 --> 00:06:33,710
Is it okay for us to peep like this?

79
00:06:33,740 --> 00:06:34,880
It's okay.

80
00:06:35,190 --> 00:06:37,360
As long as we don't disturb her.

81
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,710
She indeed has profound skills.

82
00:06:38,820 --> 00:06:39,830
As expected from

83
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:41,380
the famous Madam Mieqing in the Martial Arts World.

84
00:06:42,260 --> 00:06:42,970
What?

85
00:06:45,650 --> 00:06:48,180
Right, we respect her.

86
00:06:48,450 --> 00:06:51,050
But there have been rumors about her in the Martial Arts World,

87
00:06:51,159 --> 00:06:52,860
calling her Madam Mieqing.

88
00:06:53,210 --> 00:06:55,850
People love to spread falsehoods.

89
00:06:56,659 --> 00:06:59,540
So what's the truth about the rumors in the Martial Arts World?

90
00:07:00,350 --> 00:07:02,340
We did a lot of chivalrous things.

91
00:07:02,570 --> 00:07:04,940
But of course, we also killed a lot of people.

92
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:08,180
So we offended many people.

93
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:10,380
Yinniang

94
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:13,070
struggled to support the whole Mingyi Manor alone

95
00:07:13,530 --> 00:07:15,350
to protect us kids.

96
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:18,370
She struggled to stay alive among various forces in the Martial Arts World.

97
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:20,950
Besides her mastery of martial arts,

98
00:07:21,070 --> 00:07:23,320
she's actually

99
00:07:23,350 --> 00:07:24,620
just an ordinary woman.

100
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:28,480
Maybe you'd think I'm saying this to gain your sympathy,

101
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:32,000
but I think everyone

102
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:33,730
has something to be sympathized with.

103
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:35,840
You beat my father, didn't you?

104
00:07:38,550 --> 00:07:39,880
I don't sympathize with you.

105
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,530
My father is still imprisoned by you,

106
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:44,130
so we're still enemies.

107
00:07:44,159 --> 00:07:45,530
Everyone's position is different,

108
00:07:46,159 --> 00:07:47,610
so they naturally have different views.

109
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:50,770
That's why they kill each other.

110
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,490
Kill each other?

111
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:54,750
Isn't the fight among people

112
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,530
just killing each other?

113
00:08:15,690 --> 00:08:16,250
Thank you.

114
00:08:17,010 --> 00:08:18,970
You're so generous today.

115
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,240
What do you know?

116
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:23,090
It smells pretty good.

117
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:31,550
Boss.

118
00:08:32,260 --> 00:08:34,240
I see there're new designs for the sachets.

119
00:08:34,260 --> 00:08:36,809
These sachets seem a bit different.

120
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,179
The original ones had been sold out,

121
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,500
so I bought new fabrics.

122
00:08:40,530 --> 00:08:42,299
That's why they look different.

123
00:08:44,660 --> 00:08:46,760
I didn't expect your sachets to sell so fast.

124
00:08:47,310 --> 00:08:50,130
It seems people like me who don't know how to do needlework

125
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:51,420
are not a minority.

126
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:52,770
Actually,

127
00:08:52,950 --> 00:08:55,130
most girls make sachets themselves.

128
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:56,480
Few girls would buy these.

129
00:08:56,790 --> 00:08:58,130
They're basically bought by men

130
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,650
as gifts to women.

131
00:09:00,730 --> 00:09:03,940
Normally, sachets

132
00:09:03,990 --> 00:09:05,430
are tokens of love

133
00:09:05,430 --> 00:09:07,190
girls give to boys.

134
00:09:07,470 --> 00:09:08,780
Why don't you buy me one?

135
00:09:18,890 --> 00:09:19,870
Is that so?

136
00:09:25,260 --> 00:09:26,700
Why are you smiling?

137
00:09:27,530 --> 00:09:29,350
I'm a wanderer.

138
00:09:29,370 --> 00:09:31,390
Isn't it normal that I don't know how to do needlework?

139
00:09:32,990 --> 00:09:34,330
This one looks pretty too.

140
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:39,710
What's wrong?

141
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:41,400
Nothing.

142
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:45,770
I just feel a bit sad all of a sudden.

143
00:09:48,010 --> 00:09:50,090
You feel a bit sad all of a sudden?

144
00:09:57,860 --> 00:09:58,840
Young Master Wang.

145
00:09:59,570 --> 00:10:02,380
Can't you change your habit of being overly sympathetic?

146
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:04,230
This is annoying.

147
00:10:05,290 --> 00:10:06,030
Also, don't always

148
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:07,440
be in a daze, okay?

149
00:10:07,680 --> 00:10:10,580
Where did the dashing and smart you go?

150
00:10:14,410 --> 00:10:15,380
You know what?

151
00:10:15,810 --> 00:10:16,820
Actually,

152
00:10:17,070 --> 00:10:19,420
most people don't like to be pitied.

153
00:10:19,860 --> 00:10:21,880
Even if they're in a plight,

154
00:10:21,980 --> 00:10:24,340
they don't necessarily think it's scary.

155
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:27,390
Otherwise, people may collapse at any time.

156
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:32,060
Do you understand what I mean now that I put it this way?

157
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:38,180
Maybe I've really become stupid.

158
00:10:38,710 --> 00:10:40,240
I even forgot the simple truth that

159
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:42,270
showing kindness may cause resentment.

160
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:43,130
It's okay.

161
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:44,850
I'm not a very sensitive person.

162
00:10:44,870 --> 00:10:45,660
You don't have to be nervous.

163
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:46,350
It's not like that.

164
00:10:47,420 --> 00:10:48,640
Sympathy and kindness

165
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:50,430
should not be shown in the first place.

166
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,670
Otherwise, it would be a show of superiority.

167
00:10:52,990 --> 00:10:54,290
It would cause resentment.

168
00:10:56,570 --> 00:10:57,420
Of course,

169
00:10:57,520 --> 00:10:58,980
I don't mean that towards you.

170
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:00,350
Me too.

171
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:02,230
I've never resented you.

172
00:11:05,570 --> 00:11:07,630
Maybe I've been living too comfortably.

173
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:09,830
When I think of those sufferings,

174
00:11:10,540 --> 00:11:12,390
I feel like I can't bear them.

175
00:11:15,790 --> 00:11:16,880
How should I put it?

176
00:11:17,950 --> 00:11:20,190
As the saying goes, once you've seen the ocean, you can never settle for a pond.

177
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:23,200
It's always harder

178
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:24,560
to go from extravagance to frugality.

179
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:26,020
Actually,

180
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:28,910
I've never seen anyone who is truly happy.

181
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,980
No matter how high their status is or how rich they are,

182
00:11:32,050 --> 00:11:33,300
they're all actually the same.

183
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:35,160
People at the bottom of society

184
00:11:35,180 --> 00:11:37,330
suffer more physically,

185
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:39,180
like enduring hunger,

186
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:40,700
while rich people

187
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,170
suffer more psychologically.

188
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:45,120
They also suffer.

189
00:11:46,260 --> 00:11:48,240
People are always like this.

190
00:11:48,990 --> 00:11:51,850
They always seek troubles even when they have no troubles.

191
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:55,540
I haven't had much contact with very wealthy people.

192
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:57,310
But after hearing what you said,

193
00:11:58,450 --> 00:12:00,000
I think all beings must be suffering equally.

194
00:12:03,410 --> 00:12:04,300
Wait for me.

195
00:12:05,770 --> 00:12:10,810
[Lover's Tears]

196
00:12:08,190 --> 00:12:09,340
Glutinous rice balls. They are very sweet.

197
00:12:09,370 --> 00:12:10,610
-Delicious skewers.
-Come on.

198
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:11,600
One penny for a skewer.

199
00:12:11,670 --> 00:12:12,750
It's quite lively here today.

200
00:12:13,650 --> 00:12:15,030
Delicious skewers. Check it out.

201
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:16,610
Sir, please check this out.

202
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:18,900
Have a taste.

203
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,290
Try my spicy hotpot.

204
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,550
One penny for a skewer.

205
00:12:21,620 --> 00:12:23,360
When I saw this stall a few days ago,

206
00:12:23,390 --> 00:12:24,090
there weren't many people here.

207
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:24,860
Yes.

208
00:12:24,890 --> 00:12:25,870
I didn't expect

209
00:12:25,890 --> 00:12:27,390
these people to change so much.

210
00:12:28,420 --> 00:12:30,520
Come on, try this. Check it out.

211
00:12:30,660 --> 00:12:31,770
Let's look around.

212
00:12:32,050 --> 00:12:36,030
Didn't those beautiful girls come with you?

213
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:37,640
They didn't come today.

214
00:12:40,620 --> 00:12:41,530
Gan Pu.

215
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:43,410
It's almost noon.

216
00:12:43,570 --> 00:12:45,590
Why don't we eat something here?

217
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:47,260
If you two eat here,

218
00:12:47,290 --> 00:12:48,910
I'll let you have everything you want for free.

219
00:12:48,940 --> 00:12:50,010
All free.

220
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:53,400
Nonsense. Nonsense.

221
00:13:10,470 --> 00:13:11,920
For free?

222
00:13:12,180 --> 00:13:13,720
It's a must.

223
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:15,480
They made great contributions

224
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:16,630
and brought us a lot of business.

225
00:13:16,630 --> 00:13:17,980
It's all thanks to them.

226
00:13:18,010 --> 00:13:18,880
Really?

227
00:13:19,690 --> 00:13:22,120
So they were the ones dressed weirdly that day?

228
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,350
But they aren't wear those clothes today.

229
00:13:24,370 --> 00:13:25,380
Are we still letting them eat for free?

230
00:13:25,410 --> 00:13:27,700
Why are you as petty as your mom?

231
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:28,460
But...

232
00:13:28,890 --> 00:13:30,610
Don't we have the same mother?

233
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,500
I'm as generous as my father.

234
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:33,590
Beat him.

235
00:13:33,620 --> 00:13:34,850
Alright. Alright.

236
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,830
We'll have the regular version.

237
00:13:36,910 --> 00:13:38,190
Lover's Tears is too spicy.

238
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:39,420
No problem.

239
00:13:39,450 --> 00:13:41,890
But you have to eat Lover's Tears.

240
00:13:42,370 --> 00:13:43,160
Why?

241
00:13:43,180 --> 00:13:44,700
Because you're a man.

242
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:47,880
Men have to eat Lover's Tears?

243
00:13:48,110 --> 00:13:49,120
Why is that?

244
00:13:49,140 --> 00:13:50,270
No reason.

245
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:51,610
What do you mean no reason?

246
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:53,600
So what do you mean no reason?

247
00:13:53,650 --> 00:13:56,310
"No reason" means it's unreasonable.

248
00:13:56,650 --> 00:13:58,830
Isn't that what the ghosts said yesterday?

249
00:13:58,860 --> 00:14:00,510
They are the ghosts!

250
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:02,280
Don't you understand?

251
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:04,260
Gan Pu.

252
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:07,040
I just don't understand.

253
00:14:07,330 --> 00:14:10,050
Where did this unreasonable disaster come from?

254
00:14:10,180 --> 00:14:12,680
Who knows? They're so weird.

255
00:14:14,810 --> 00:14:17,210
Gan Pu, how many skewers do you want?

256
00:14:17,310 --> 00:14:19,520
I'll have three to five.

257
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:20,750
I can't eat a lot.

258
00:14:21,390 --> 00:14:22,190
Okay.

259
00:14:22,230 --> 00:14:24,290
Please give us ten skewers then.

260
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:26,420
Are you sure?

261
00:14:27,540 --> 00:14:28,610
What do you mean?

262
00:14:29,150 --> 00:14:31,560
When we give food away for free, there's a rule.

263
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:34,850
You'll have to finish all ten skewers.

264
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:36,350
If you can't finish them,

265
00:14:36,380 --> 00:14:38,310
you'll have to shout in the street

266
00:14:38,330 --> 00:14:39,060
that you're not a man.

267
00:14:39,090 --> 00:14:40,990
And you have to do it ten times.

268
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:49,860
Have I ever offended you?

269
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:50,610
No, no.

270
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:51,640
You are our benefactor.

271
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:52,980
How could you have offended us?

272
00:14:53,010 --> 00:14:54,050
Benefactor.

273
00:14:56,420 --> 00:14:57,380
You win.

274
00:14:58,680 --> 00:15:00,800
So I fell into your trap.

275
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:04,480
I'd like to see

276
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:06,590
what you have up your sleeves.

277
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:09,330
Come and take a look.

278
00:15:09,350 --> 00:15:11,140
This gentleman here said he'd eat ten skewers

279
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:12,480
of our Lover's Tears.

280
00:15:12,510 --> 00:15:15,260
If he can't finish them, he'll claim he's not a man.

281
