00:26:54,650 --> 00:26:56,950
I'd wear men's clothes when it was inconvenient.

565
00:26:57,260 --> 00:26:57,980
You...

566
00:26:59,380 --> 00:27:00,330
You've all dressed up as men before?

567
00:27:00,360 --> 00:27:01,160
No.

568
00:27:03,910 --> 00:27:04,880
I have.

569
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:21,530
Why are you back?

570
00:27:22,650 --> 00:27:23,700
Well,

571
00:27:23,970 --> 00:27:25,200
I accept your suggestion.

572
00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:26,750
I've come around.

573
00:27:27,010 --> 00:27:28,230
What suggestion?

574
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:30,180
You said it to me this morning.

575
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:30,970
Did you already forget?

576
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:34,920
No way.

577
00:27:36,170 --> 00:27:37,090
Why not?

578
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:38,740
I was already

579
00:27:38,770 --> 00:27:41,280
ready to leave the town,

580
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:43,270
but Young Master Wang went to see me

581
00:27:43,630 --> 00:27:44,850
and persuaded me to come back.

582
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:49,810
You came back just because he persuaded you?

583
00:27:50,260 --> 00:27:51,680
Didn't you say you didn't care?

584
00:27:52,440 --> 00:27:53,480
Are you going back on your word?

585
00:27:56,550 --> 00:27:57,780
Anyway, I've made up my mind.

586
00:27:58,060 --> 00:28:00,020
I'll stay here for my goal.

587
00:28:00,460 --> 00:28:01,100
Besides,

588
00:28:01,370 --> 00:28:03,700
I think your suggestion actually works.

589
00:28:03,810 --> 00:28:06,940
Covering an old relationship with a new one.

590
00:28:07,910 --> 00:28:08,510
It's clever.

591
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:09,640
Thank you.

592
00:28:10,250 --> 00:28:12,800
How can you do that so fast?

593
00:28:13,740 --> 00:28:16,110
This way, I won't be in pain.

594
00:28:16,610 --> 00:28:18,100
Don't you want me to be happy?

595
00:28:21,130 --> 00:28:22,080
Let's continue with the class.

596
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:24,980
Alright.

597
00:28:25,350 --> 00:28:27,370
Now, let's practice walking.

598
00:28:27,790 --> 00:28:30,420
Try to find the charm of men's walking.

599
00:28:30,470 --> 00:28:32,360
What charm do men have when they walk?

600
00:28:32,390 --> 00:28:35,350
Don't men all stagger when they walk?

601
00:28:36,670 --> 00:28:37,540
Come on. Start walking.

602
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:07,760
They all seem to be familiar with men's clothes.

603
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:10,200
Besides Hu Jiao and Qing Cai,

604
00:29:11,770 --> 00:29:14,610
Gao Yin and Gan Pu wear men's clothes quite a lot.

605
00:29:16,430 --> 00:29:18,680
As for Han Aizhen...

606
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:21,830
Like this.

607
00:29:22,130 --> 00:29:23,950
Maybe it's because of her personality.

608
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:25,980
Go that way. That way.

609
00:29:26,010 --> 00:29:28,180
Hu Jiao looks carefree.

610
00:29:28,530 --> 00:29:29,880
Why is she walking like this?

611
00:29:32,460 --> 00:29:34,090
She does look a bit strange.

612
00:29:36,040 --> 00:29:37,190
Look.

613
00:29:37,220 --> 00:29:38,780
Why is she walking like this?

614
00:29:41,070 --> 00:29:43,400
Why is Qing Cai walking so strangely?

615
00:29:43,560 --> 00:29:45,060
If all men walk like this,

616
00:29:45,080 --> 00:29:46,160
I won't like men anymore.

617
00:29:46,340 --> 00:29:47,300
Good.

618
00:29:47,330 --> 00:29:49,180
Then stop liking men.

619
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:51,470
Leave Wang Yishao to me to like.

620
00:29:51,910 --> 00:29:53,730
What's the use of me leaving him to you?

621
00:29:53,770 --> 00:29:54,700
So many people

622
00:29:54,730 --> 00:29:56,130
like Young Master Wang.

623
00:30:06,380 --> 00:30:07,400
Qing Cai.

624
00:30:07,430 --> 00:30:08,230
You used to

625
00:30:08,270 --> 00:30:10,600
refuse to recognize yourself as a woman.

626
00:30:10,860 --> 00:30:12,220
Why are you

627
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:14,050
so averse to men now?

628
00:30:15,700 --> 00:30:17,200
You cold-faced girl.

629
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:18,940
When did you change your character

630
00:30:18,970 --> 00:30:20,410
and start to tease others?

631
00:30:21,330 --> 00:30:23,300
I'm just trying to get closer to you.

632
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:25,820
I don't want to cause any bloody incident

633
00:30:25,850 --> 00:30:27,330
just because we don't know each other well.

634
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:30,000
Indeed.

635
00:30:30,070 --> 00:30:32,120
We should find a chance to talk.

636
00:30:32,980 --> 00:30:33,850
Okay.

637
00:30:34,390 --> 00:30:35,640
After this is done,

638
00:30:36,560 --> 00:30:37,600
let's have a deep chat.

639
00:30:39,040 --> 00:30:39,560
Alright.

640
00:30:41,410 --> 00:30:43,680
In the future,

641
00:30:43,750 --> 00:30:45,790
our courses will no longer be conducted in the form of classes.

642
00:30:45,820 --> 00:30:47,890
Instead, it'll be integrated into your lives.

643
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:49,100
You mean

644
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:50,990
we have to keep wearing men's clothes?

645
00:30:52,950 --> 00:30:54,340
Not really.

646
00:30:54,950 --> 00:30:56,510
After you really understand

647
00:30:56,540 --> 00:30:57,980
the charm of men,

648
00:30:58,160 --> 00:31:00,230
you can experience other people's lives.

649
00:31:00,450 --> 00:31:02,510
For example, just as I mentioned before,

650
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:05,150
you can experience what it's like to be a fool,

651
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:06,970
a beggar,

652
00:31:07,040 --> 00:31:08,080
or a lunatic, and so on.

653
00:31:08,810 --> 00:31:10,150
How boring that is!

654
00:31:11,350 --> 00:31:13,240
It's better to be a man.

655
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:15,630
At least it's not that annoying.

656
00:31:18,120 --> 00:31:20,600
I'll stay at Mingyi Manor

657
00:31:20,740 --> 00:31:21,940
and instruct you...

658
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:25,840
You guys anytime.

659
00:31:27,040 --> 00:31:28,570
I think you just want to find a way

660
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:30,120
to not leave Mingyi Manor.

661
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:32,040
That's not true.

662
00:31:33,610 --> 00:31:35,310
You dare to do it, but not admit it?

663
00:31:35,490 --> 00:31:36,550
I look down on you.

664
00:31:44,900 --> 00:31:46,640
That's all for today's lesson.

665
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:48,280
There will be new classes tomorrow.

666
00:31:48,470 --> 00:31:49,660
You're dismissed.

667
00:31:50,150 --> 00:31:50,840
Gan Pu.

668
00:31:53,100 --> 00:31:54,090
Do you have time?

669
00:31:54,730 --> 00:31:56,310
Come to my place to have some tea.

670
00:31:56,530 --> 00:31:56,970
Sure.

671
00:31:57,150 --> 00:31:58,600
You... You've recovered?

672
00:31:59,110 --> 00:31:59,790
I feel alright now.

673
00:32:00,490 --> 00:32:02,130
I just feel a bit miserable today.

674
00:32:02,170 --> 00:32:03,900
I feel like I fell into the bandits' den.

675
00:32:04,150 --> 00:32:05,620
But I'm happy.

676
00:32:06,050 --> 00:32:07,730
They are not real bandits.

677
00:32:07,750 --> 00:32:09,050
When they see their boss,

678
00:32:09,070 --> 00:32:10,230
they'll be as obedient as little lambs.

679
00:32:13,230 --> 00:32:15,200
Would you like to have tea at Wang Yishao's?

680
00:32:15,420 --> 00:32:16,990
I have plans with Qing Cai.

681
00:32:17,010 --> 00:32:18,280
I'll pass.

682
00:32:20,420 --> 00:32:21,770
When did you two

683
00:32:21,780 --> 00:32:22,870
hook up?

684
00:32:22,950 --> 00:32:23,920
It's weird.

685
00:32:26,550 --> 00:32:27,560
Don't talk nonsense.

686
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:28,970
We have things to talk about.

687
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:31,720
Han Aizhen.

688
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:33,660
I don't want to have tea.

689
00:32:33,860 --> 00:32:35,340
The tea tastes terrible.

690
00:32:36,180 --> 00:32:37,170
Let's go hunting.

691
00:32:37,230 --> 00:32:39,360
Jiaoniang has run out of food.

692
00:32:39,390 --> 00:32:40,110
Sure.

693
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:41,490
Anyway,

694
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:43,930
I don't want to drink tea either.

695
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:44,760
Let's go.

696
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:45,360
Let's go.

697
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:48,060
Let's go and have tea.

698
00:32:48,090 --> 00:32:48,650
Let's go.

699
00:32:55,780 --> 00:32:58,330
Han Aizhen, be careful not to get bitten by a snake again in the mountain.

700
00:32:58,640 --> 00:32:59,410
It'll bite you.

701
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:02,970
Han Aizhen, stop right there!

702
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:32,690
Let's go. Don't get in their way.

703
00:33:32,710 --> 00:33:33,510
Let's go have a drink.

704
00:33:35,850 --> 00:33:36,840
They're going to have a drink.

705
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:42,650
Please.

706
00:33:44,230 --> 00:33:45,720
Han Aizhen has told me.

707
00:33:46,280 --> 00:33:47,450
I understand what you mean.

708
00:33:49,020 --> 00:33:50,990
But your mask is too heavy.

709
00:33:51,290 --> 00:33:52,650
It always makes me feel

710
00:33:53,330 --> 00:33:55,580
there's a knife hanging there.

711
00:33:56,780 --> 00:33:58,150
As your enemy,

712
00:33:59,230 --> 00:34:01,170
I know your most important secret.

713
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:03,210
Now,

714
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:05,740
I've also found out your identity.

715
00:34:06,830 --> 00:34:08,110
You're indeed

716
00:34:09,050 --> 00:34:11,090
facing a life-and-death crisis now.

717
00:34:13,330 --> 00:34:14,429
From my point of view,

718
00:34:15,860 --> 00:34:18,389
you are a very dangerous monster.

719
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:20,489
I'll either kill you

720
00:34:21,300 --> 00:34:22,620
or run away.

721
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:26,840
You take such a big risk staying here.

722
00:34:27,190 --> 00:34:28,449
Is it just to save

723
00:34:29,320 --> 00:34:30,949
your foster father who's imprisoned here?

724
00:34:32,010 --> 00:34:32,560
Yes.

725
00:34:35,060 --> 00:34:36,010
Now,

726
00:34:36,510 --> 00:34:39,090
I'll unveil the thickest mask in your mind.

727
00:34:45,639 --> 00:34:48,080
You're not showing your real intention of killing me now, are you?

728
00:34:49,760 --> 00:34:50,560
Here?

729
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:56,929
Did you choose the wrong place?

730
00:34:57,510 --> 00:34:59,510
I just want to sort out

731
00:34:59,810 --> 00:35:01,470
our core conflict with you.

732
00:35:01,510 --> 00:35:02,660
Core conflict?

733
00:35:04,930 --> 00:35:06,140
We're in different camps.

734
00:35:07,540 --> 00:35:08,900
I'm the one who will subvert you.

735
00:35:09,560 --> 00:35:10,950
That's your identity,

736
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:12,200
not who you are.

737
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:17,850
I came here only to save my father.

738
00:35:17,990 --> 00:35:19,130
As for other matters,

739
00:35:19,460 --> 00:35:20,500
I'm not interested at all.

740
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:22,830
So what core conflict do we have?

741
00:35:28,180 --> 00:35:29,690
No matter how far an ant goes,

742
00:35:31,410 --> 00:35:32,670
it has to go home.

743
00:35:35,560 --> 00:35:37,460
Maybe one ant went too far

744
00:35:39,390 --> 00:35:41,100
and forgot the way home.

745
00:35:44,720 --> 00:35:46,470
You really saw through me.

746
00:35:47,030 --> 00:35:48,220
But the people on your side

747
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:49,270
won't think so.

748
00:35:49,460 --> 00:35:51,790
Their first priority will still be to kill me.

749
00:35:53,060 --> 00:35:54,590
That's why I kept silent.

750
00:35:56,560 --> 00:35:57,620
Can I trust you?

751
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:01,830
Just like how a mouse believes that a cat won't eat it?

752
00:36:03,170 --> 00:36:04,180
So what do you think?

753
00:36:05,250 --> 00:36:07,320
Why haven't I exposed you?

754
00:36:07,980 --> 00:36:08,940
Do you think

755
00:36:09,820 --> 00:36:11,990
I'm playing a cat-and-mouse game?

756
00:36:13,060 --> 00:36:13,940
Give me a reason.

757
00:36:17,090 --> 00:36:18,420
We are all pawns.

758
00:36:22,070 --> 00:36:22,910
Those who are fighting against each other

759
00:36:24,350 --> 00:36:25,420
are not us.

760
00:36:27,820 --> 00:36:29,060
People fight

761
00:36:30,040 --> 00:36:32,740
just to get more things.

762
00:36:33,710 --> 00:36:34,970
It's like playing chess.

763
00:36:35,040 --> 00:36:37,240
But we are not players.

764
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:41,000
To win or to lose is their business.

765
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:44,280
With your ability,

766
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,360
you don't look like a pawn.

767
00:36:47,040 --> 00:36:48,230
I think

768
00:36:49,980 --> 00:36:51,280
you are more like

769
00:36:51,970 --> 00:36:54,260
a pawn that wants to destroy the entire chessboard.

770
00:36:57,570 --> 00:37:00,490
You mentioned those people's boss.

771
00:37:00,950 --> 00:37:01,680
Do you know him?

772
00:37:02,810 --> 00:37:03,890
Of course.

773
00:37:04,090 --> 00:37:06,900
I have a special relationship with him.

774
00:37:07,990 --> 00:37:09,820
One of them said

775
00:37:10,030 --> 00:37:13,750
I stole a man from their boss.

776
00:37:14,200 --> 00:37:15,040
What does that mean?

777
00:37:18,130 --> 00:37:20,050
Is their boss a woman?

778
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:25,120
Why are you laughing?

779
00:37:25,560 --> 00:37:26,820
I'm laughing.

780
00:37:27,370 --> 00:37:29,280
I'm laughing because

781
00:37:29,300 --> 00:37:30,800
you finally look a bit human now.

782
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:32,390
What was I like before?

783
00:37:32,590 --> 00:37:33,730
Before...

784
00:37:33,750 --> 00:37:35,280
You used to be fairy-like.

785
00:37:35,290 --> 00:37:36,950
You'd make people feel they couldn't get close to you.

786
00:37:37,150 --> 00:37:39,090
Didn't we work together?

787
00:37:39,570 --> 00:37:41,530
Why did you still think I was inhumane?

788
00:37:41,760 --> 00:37:43,440
That was just superficial.

789
00:37:43,650 --> 00:37:45,070
It felt like you were pretending.

790
00:37:50,320 --> 00:37:53,910
Would you only feel real when I'm being tortured?

791
00:37:56,280 --> 00:37:57,670
You're not really thinking about

792
00:37:57,710 --> 00:37:59,080
how you want to be tortured, are you?

793
00:37:59,630 --> 00:38:00,850
No.

794
00:38:01,650 --> 00:38:03,290
You may be well-educated,

795
00:38:04,040 --> 00:38:06,260
but your mentality is still like that of a child.

796
00:38:08,880 --> 00:38:11,540
Is this a compliment or a scolding?

797
00:38:11,720 --> 00:38:12,480
Look at you.

798
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:15,110
I called you a fool, and you really became a fool?

799
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:16,850
Forget it.

800
00:38:17,720 --> 00:38:20,130
In order for you to return to your former smart and unrestrained self,

801
00:38:20,210 --> 00:38:21,470
I have to stay away from you.

802
00:38:22,140 --> 00:38:23,250
Don't.

803
00:38:23,520 --> 00:38:25,960
We can still be friends.

804
00:38:28,050 --> 00:38:30,480
Based on my past experience,

805
00:38:31,150 --> 00:38:34,250
many people who say we should start off as friends

806
00:38:34,580 --> 00:38:37,120
have other intentions later.

807
00:38:37,890 --> 00:38:38,840
This...

808
00:38:43,430 --> 00:38:44,600
Alright, alright.

809
00:38:44,630 --> 00:38:45,570
I was just kidding.

810
00:38:47,020 --> 00:38:48,110
You

811
00:38:48,140 --> 00:38:49,340
are really a good person.

812
00:38:49,910 --> 00:38:52,180
How about I take you as my older brother?

813
00:38:52,230 --> 00:38:53,180
In case you

814
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:54,340
have improper thoughts about me in the future.

815
00:38:54,360 --> 00:38:55,520
But... But I...

816
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:57,540
Stop stammering.

817
00:38:57,560 --> 00:38:58,440
It's a deal.

818
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:01,910
How should I address you in the future?

819
00:39:01,940 --> 00:39:02,940
No, no.

820
00:39:03,630 --> 00:39:07,830
I haven't come around yet.

821
00:39:07,850 --> 00:39:09,510
Stop stammering.

822
00:39:09,910 --> 00:39:10,760
It's a deal.

823
00:39:10,780 --> 00:39:12,750
Let me think about how I should address you first.

824
00:39:13,060 --> 00:39:15,710
How about Young Master Wang?

825
00:39:15,770 --> 00:39:16,400
No.

826
00:39:16,430 --> 00:39:18,040
That's too distant.

827
00:39:18,690 --> 00:39:20,470
Second Prince?

828
00:39:20,990 --> 00:39:22,840
Second Prince is even more distant.

829
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:26,840
How about I call you Brother?

830
00:39:28,070 --> 00:39:30,200
It's so cheesy. I can't say it out.

831
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:33,370
Brother Wang. Brother Wang...

832
00:39:33,400 --> 00:39:34,720
It's so markety.

833
00:39:35,420 --> 00:39:36,100
How about Big Wang?

834
00:39:36,540 --> 00:39:37,390
Wait, wait.

835
00:39:37,420 --> 00:39:39,030
Give me a bit more time.

836
00:39:39,110 --> 00:39:39,870
Or...

837
00:39:40,490 --> 00:39:42,850
Maybe you can call me

838
00:39:44,700 --> 00:39:45,540
Handsome Wang?

839
00:39:45,570 --> 00:39:46,410
Handsome Wang.

840
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:49,670
Handsome Wang.

841
00:39:49,690 --> 00:39:52,600
But don't let others know about this for now.

842
00:39:53,160 --> 00:39:54,680
Okay, it's just between the two of us.

843
00:39:55,710 --> 00:39:56,890
Handsome Wang...

844
00:40:02,220 --> 00:40:03,790
Lower your voice.

845
00:40:05,110 --> 00:40:06,650
It's low enough.

846
00:40:10,240 --> 00:40:11,130
Don't.

847
00:40:18,820 --> 00:40:20,310
Over there. Hurry up.

848
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:22,970
Over there.

849
00:40:25,900 --> 00:40:26,780
Where?

850
00:40:27,420 --> 00:40:28,440
Stop cutting! Stop it!

851
00:40:28,490 --> 00:40:30,390
You're almost chopping it into pieces.

852
00:40:31,610 --> 00:40:33,450
Are you sure it was a rabbit?

853
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:35,360
It left a shadow and ran away.

854
00:40:35,710 --> 00:40:36,920
I think so.

855
00:40:36,940 --> 00:40:39,040
What if it was a rat?

856
00:40:39,070 --> 00:40:40,320
It was just a shadow.

857
00:40:40,350 --> 00:40:42,090
How would I know?

858
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:43,890
I didn't see it.

859
00:40:52,370 --> 00:40:53,860
Don't. Don't.

860
00:40:54,830 --> 00:40:55,870
You saw it again?

861
00:40:55,910 --> 00:40:56,510
No.

862
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:58,130
I was just kidding you.

863
00:41:00,170 --> 00:41:01,970
You think you can catch rabbits this way?

864
00:41:02,040 --> 00:41:04,140
Why do they always succeed in hunting?

865
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:05,800
Gan Pu knows how to set a trap.

866
00:41:05,820 --> 00:41:07,240
Of course she can catch prey.

867
00:41:08,570 --> 00:41:09,330
That makes sense.

868
00:41:09,340 --> 00:41:11,000
Let's ask Gan Pu for help next time.

869
00:41:11,040 --> 00:41:13,440
Don't use your sword anymore. We won't succeed.

870
00:41:13,690 --> 00:41:14,920
Are we quitting?

871
00:41:15,050 --> 00:41:15,840
Yes, let's quit.

872
00:41:15,860 --> 00:41:16,860
It hurts so much.

873
00:41:17,250 --> 00:41:19,080
Don't chop it with your sword next time.

874
00:41:19,190 --> 00:41:20,470
The rabbit can't be eaten that way.

875
00:41:23,620 --> 00:41:25,740
You drink like this every day.

876
00:41:25,980 --> 00:41:27,580
Why haven't you become wasted?

877
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:29,380
I'm a wine jar.

878
00:41:30,230 --> 00:41:32,660
I can hold my liquor. I never get drunk.

879
00:41:33,190 --> 00:41:35,800
How could a wine jar be damaged by wine?

880
00:41:39,230 --> 00:41:40,720
In this weather,

881
00:41:40,970 --> 00:41:43,560
we are both men, yet we're sitting on this mountain together.

882
00:41:43,680 --> 00:41:44,910
It's foggy and misty.

883
00:41:44,980 --> 00:41:46,520
It's quite romantic.

884
00:41:46,540 --> 00:41:47,880
Isn't it a bit awkward?

885
00:41:47,910 --> 00:41:49,780
It's better to go down the mountain and enjoy the sunshine.

886
00:41:50,540 --> 00:41:51,850
Hey.

887
00:41:53,110 --> 00:41:55,260
Did you go peek at the girls taking a shower?

888
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:56,280
I didn't.

889
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:59,580
Would I have been beaten if I peeked?

890
00:42:00,130 --> 00:42:02,170
You even got beaten up by girls.

891
00:42:02,190 --> 00:42:04,060
How did you end up like this?

892
00:42:04,670 --> 00:42:06,330
After that incident,

893
00:42:06,810 --> 00:42:08,600
I didn't follow them much.

894
00:42:08,620 --> 00:42:10,760
Whenever I see someone going in the direction of the shower room,

895
00:42:10,790 --> 00:42:11,970
I'll give up right away.

896
00:42:14,580 --> 00:42:16,350
Since when

897
00:42:16,750 --> 00:42:18,610
did you side with Wang Yishao?

898
00:42:18,630 --> 00:42:20,140
Is it because of that woman?

899
00:42:22,450 --> 00:42:24,330
I just couldn't bear to see him degenerate.

900
00:42:24,790 --> 00:42:26,090
As his friend,

901
00:42:26,950 --> 00:42:28,450
I just gave him a little help.

902
00:42:29,520 --> 00:42:30,810
Let me ask you something.

903
00:42:31,160 --> 00:42:33,690
Do you really think Qing Cai,

904
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:35,560
I mean, Vegetable,

905
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:37,440
is a woman?

906
00:42:37,930 --> 00:42:39,250
What do you mean?

907
00:42:40,030 --> 00:42:41,460
You really don't understand?

908
00:42:43,820 --> 00:42:45,760
That's a man.

909
00:42:45,970 --> 00:42:47,450
H-How is that possible?

910
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:48,870
What do you mean how is that possible?

911
00:42:49,290 --> 00:42:50,900
You're just too naive.

912
00:42:51,500 --> 00:42:52,530
Unlike me.

913
00:42:56,840 --> 00:42:59,510
You go through various girls, yet never get involved with them?

914
00:43:02,080 --> 00:43:03,010
Let me tell you.

915
00:43:03,210 --> 00:43:04,600
To judge if someone is a woman,

916
00:43:04,880 --> 00:43:06,390
use your smell. If it's a woman, you can smell it

917
00:43:06,500 --> 00:43:09,170
when she walks by.

918
00:43:09,430 --> 00:43:12,420
You can also identity women's personalities

919
00:43:12,440 --> 00:43:15,050
through how they smell.

920
00:43:16,650 --> 00:43:18,190
This is the

921
00:43:18,220 --> 00:43:20,500
valuable experience I've summarized over the years.

922
00:43:20,510 --> 00:43:21,960
Are you serious?

923
00:43:29,150 --> 00:43:29,790
They...

924
00:43:31,560 --> 00:43:32,940
They take baths together,

925
00:43:33,850 --> 00:43:35,270
and they sleep together.

926
00:43:36,180 --> 00:43:37,790
How could she be a man?

927
00:43:38,070 --> 00:43:40,730
All you know is they take baths together,

928
00:43:40,760 --> 00:43:41,710
and you ruined it.

929
00:43:41,740 --> 00:43:43,980
What else do you know?

930
00:43:48,320 --> 00:43:50,980
No wonder Sun Li kept sniffing around him.

931
00:43:54,670 --> 00:43:56,970
Why do you smell like a man?

932
00:44:02,460 --> 00:44:05,060
Isn't that Gao Yin a doctor?

933
00:44:05,090 --> 00:44:05,650
Yes.

934
00:44:06,680 --> 00:44:07,940
So

935
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:10,740
he also knows he's a man?

936
00:44:11,050 --> 00:44:12,590
Of course Gao Yin knows.

937
00:44:13,060 --> 00:44:15,400
She and Qing Cai seem to have formed

938
00:44:15,420 --> 00:44:16,940
a special tacit understanding.

939
00:44:17,720 --> 00:44:18,690
Today,

940
00:44:18,720 --> 00:44:20,650
they made an appointment to negotiate, right?

941
00:44:21,140 --> 00:44:22,780
She... She...

942
00:44:22,800 --> 00:44:24,390
Doesn't she like Young Master Wang?

943
00:44:25,940 --> 00:44:27,440
Why didn't she tell Young Master Wang?

944
00:44:27,470 --> 00:44:28,800
Don't you know what kind of person Gao Yin is?

945
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:31,370
She's a woman with a strong mind.

946
00:44:31,570 --> 00:44:32,550
She's no ordinary person.

947
00:44:32,580 --> 00:44:34,500
So why didn't you tell Young Master Wang?

948
00:44:46,470 --> 00:44:48,180
Should I tell him?

949
00:44:52,130 --> 00:44:53,640
H-How could this be?

950
00:44:56,960 --> 00:44:58,460
How come he's a man?

951
00:44:58,930 --> 00:45:00,250
He's not a man.

952
00:45:00,670 --> 00:45:01,850
He's definitely not a man.

953
00:45:03,980 --> 00:45:05,900
Take your time to calm down.

954
00:45:08,600 --> 00:45:09,530
No way.

955
00:45:10,890 --> 00:45:11,780
There's no way.

956
00:45:16,010 --> 00:45:17,930
How could he possibly be a man?

957
00:45:23,740 --> 00:45:24,930
He's not a man!

958
00:45:31,310 --> 00:45:32,690
He's not a man!
